President Obama expressed his gratitude for David Medine's leadership as the Chairman of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board (PCLOB). Medine has served in this role since 2013, being the first full-time Chairman. The President highlighted the significance of Medine's tenure, which coincided with a thorough examination of national security tools and policies to ensure they align with the Administration's commitment to civil liberties and individual privacy. The President acknowledged the PCLOB's valuable analysis and input, which have consistently informed his decision-making and the work of his team. President Obama praised Medine's talent and dedication as a public servant and wished him success in his future endeavors.